{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":139429,"duration_api_ms":139143,"num_turns":30,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"8069a444-1583-4c20-97a4-58b9118e6896","total_cost_usd":0.89644925,"usage":{"input_tokens":17,"cache_creation_input_tokens":58911,"cache_read_input_tokens":731141,"output_tokens":6504,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":58911,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":17,"outputTokens":6504,"cacheReadInputTokens":731141,"cacheCreationInputTokens":58911,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.89644925,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"In `matching_finalized_task_runs` (model.rs:448-480), the `started_at` fallback path does not exclude entries whose `run_id` is `Some(different_id)`. When a caller provides `run_id = Some(\"run-3\")` and the DB has a finalized entry with `run_id = Some(\"run-2\")` at the same `started_at`, the fallback returns that entry — blocking a legitimate new run with a misleading \"already finalized\" error. The fallback filter (line 476-479) should additionally require `entry.run_id.is_none()` when `run_id` was provided, so it only catches the runless-to-named upgrade case the tests intend to cover, not a collision between two distinct named runs that happen to share a timestamp.","rationale":"This is a correctness gap. The two tests added only cover the run_id=None case. While timestamp collisions are rare in practice, the function's contract (\"match finalized attempts for this specific start request\") should not conflate distinct named runs. The fix is a single `.filter()` addition."}],"summary":"Reviewed the diff across model.rs, service.rs, and fs.rs. The changes correctly close the runless replay loophole: `has_finalized_task_run` is replaced by `matching_finalized_task_runs` which also catches entries without a run_id by falling back to `started_at`. All 108 milestone_record tests pass. One correctness gap identified: the `started_at` fallback in `matching_finalized_task_runs` can false-positive when a different named run (non-None run_id) happens to share the same timestamp, because it doesn't filter out entries with a different explicit run_id. No other bugs, safety issues, or significant maintainability risks found."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"9247a8ae-dcde-4b0d-a6be-bd48998205e8"}
